TY  - JOUR
AU  - Moraux, Franck
AU  - Navatte, Patrick
AU  - Villa, Christophe
T1  -  The Predictive Power of the French Market Volatility Index: A Multi Horizons Study *
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/01/01
DO  - 10.1023/A:1009873516217
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 2
IS  - 3
SP  - 303
EP  - 320
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - The main purpose of this paper is to examine empirically the time series properties of the French Market Volatility Index (VX1). We also examine the VX1's ability to forecast future realized market volatility and finds a strong relationship. More importantly, we show how the index can be used to generate volatility forecasts over different horizons and that these forecasts are reasonably accurate predictors of future realized volatility. JEL classification codes: G14, C53, C13.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1009873516217
ER  - 



