TY  - JOUR
AU  - Maksimovic, Vojislav
AU  - Stomper, Alex
AU  - Zechner, Josef
T1  - Capital Structure, Information Acquisition and Investment Decisions in an Industry Framework
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/01/01
DO  - 10.1023/A:1009825432146
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 2
IS  - 3
SP  - 251
EP  - 271
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This paper analyzes the relationship between a firm's capital structure and its information acquisition prior to capital budgeting decisions. It is found that low-growth industries can sustain a large number of levered firms. In these industries, leverage is negatively related to a firm's incentive to acquire information during the capital budgeting process. In contrast, high-growth industries only sustain a small number of levered firms. In these industries, levered firms acquire more information than all-equity financed firms. The model yields empirical predictions regarding the effects of leverage on the expected amount and the volatility of corporate investment.While leverage does not affect firm value, highly levered firms generate a more volatile cash flow than firms with low debt levels. JEL classification codes: G31, G32.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1009825432146
ER  - 



